What was the percentage increase in Sierra Leone's inflation from 2013 to 2020?
predicted_answer:
The percentage increase in Sierra Leone's inflation from 2013 to 2020 was approximately 3.6%.

To calculate this, we take the difference between the inflation rate in 2020 (16.862%) and the inflation rate in 2013 (12.9%), and divide it by the inflation rate in 2013. The formula is:

(2020 inflation - 2013 inflation) / 2013 inflation

This gives us:

(16.862 - 12.9) / 12.9 = 0.0358 or 3.58%

Therefore, the percentage increase in Sierra Leone's inflation from 2013 to 2020 was approximately 3.6%.
